com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.util
Interface NativeCapableFactory

public interface NativeCapableFactory

The NativeCapableFactory is the interface used as a shortcut to create native capable objects wrapping other native capable, or "can be native" objects, or primitive values.

See Also:
JNIEasy.getNativeCapableFactory()

wrapValue

CanBeNativeCapable wrapValue(java.lang.Object value)
Wraps the specified "can be native" value inside a native capable object.

The native type used is the default native type of the specified value.

Current implementation is:

if (value == null) return null; TypeCanBeNativeCapable typeDec = (TypeCanBeNativeCapable)getTypeManager().getDefaultType(value); return (CanBeNativeCapable)typeDec.wrapValue(value);
For instance:
NativeCapableFactory factory = JNIEasy.get().getObjectFactory(); NativeString obj = (NativeString)factory.wrapValue("Hello");

Parameters:
value - the object to wrap.
Returns:
the native capable object.
See Also:
NativeTypeManager.getDefaultType(Object), TypeCanBeNativeCapable.wrapValue(Object)

newPointer

NativePointer newPointer(java.lang.Object addressed)
Creates a native capable NativePointer object containing the specified reference as the contained pointer.

Current implementation uses the default native type of the parameter to construct the type of the container pointer.

Parameters:
addressed - the reference to be addressed. Can not be null.
Returns:
the new NativePointer object containing the specified reference.
See Also:
NativeTypeManager.getDefaultType(Object), TypeNative.decVarType(), VarTypeNative.decPointer(), TypeNativeObject.newValue(), NativeSingleFieldContainer.setValue(Object)

newString

NativeString newString(java.lang.String value)
Wraps (makes native capable) a String object with a NativeString wrapper object.

This method is a shortcut of TypeNativeString.newString(String)

Current implementation is:

if (value == null) return null; return getTypeManager().decString().newString(value);

Parameters:
value - the String value to wrap.
Returns:
the native capable wrapper object.
See Also:
NativeTypeManager.decString()
